Touch Calibration
Next step will do touch calibration, press confirm button and do not touch screen after it, wait for calibration success hint
Touch Calibration pass, Please use it normally
Touch Calibration failed, Please retry
start calibration
Below is OS version info. Confirm that the info highlighted in green is correct.

Cover the proximity sensor (located at the top of the phone near the receiver) with your hand, then move your hand away. The value should increase from 0.0 when you move your hand further away from the device.\nWhen calibrating, make sure there\'s nothing between the sensor and your hand (e.g. protective screen cover or gloves).
Values for X，Y，Z, coordinates should appear below
DAC value should appear below
Values for X，Y，Z, coordinates should appear below
Value for pressure should appear below
Backlight, notification light, and flash light (rear), should respond when corresponding button is pressed.
See if vibration (long and short) is functioning normally
Below is the address of the Wi-Fi network that the phone is currently connected to. Confirm that the info highlighted in green is correct.
Below is the Wi-Fi AP info of the devices in the area that were detected. Confirm that the info highlighted in green is correct.
The Bluetooth address of this device should be displayed below.
Below is the info of the Bluetooth devices that were detected nearby.

Move the device quickly in one direction. X，Y，Z coordinate values are displayed below. (when phone is in motion: X is represents left/right, y represents front/back, z represents up and down).\nBefore you calibrate the device, place it on a flat surface.
When headphones are connected, the text \"Headphones detected\" should be displayed below.
When headphones are connected, press the buttons on the headphone remote (often located on the cord). The corresponding text on screen should turn green.
When headphones are disconnected, the text \"Headphones have been disconnected\" should be displayed below
Confirm that correct the status and info of the SIM card is displayed below
This test will reboot the device. All previous test data will be lost.
Main microphone receiver feedback test\n\nHold the phone as if you are making a call, speak into the microphone and should hear your voice in the receiver.
Secondary microphone speaker feedback test.\n\nTurn the phone so that the headphone input is facing downward. Speak into the receiver. You should hear your voice played through the external speaker.
Ambient noise reduction test\n\nHold the phone as if you\'re answering a call, speak in to the microphone. You should hear your voice with reduced noise in the background played through the receiver.
Main microphone to receiver feedback test.\n\nHold the phone as if you are making a call, speak to main microphone, you should hear voice from reveiver
While wearing the headphones, connect them to the device. Speak into the headphone microphone (often located on the cord). You should hear your voice in the headphone\'s speakers.
Back microphone to speaker feedback test. \n\nTurn the phone, Speak to back microphone , you should hear voice in speaker
Simulation call test.\n\nHold the phone as if you are making a call, Speak to main microphone, you should hear voice in the receiver. do the test in silent environment
Top microphone to speaker feedback test.\n\n Turn the phone, Speak to top microphone , you should hear voice in speaker
The text \"SD card detected, remove SD card now\" should be displayed below.
When you remove the SD card, the text \"SD card has been removed, insert SD card now\" should be displayed below.
When you push the buttons, the corresponding text on screen should turn green (note: the Home and the Power buttons are not included in the test).
When USB charger is connected the text \"Charging via USB/AC\" should be displayed below.
When USB charger is disconnected the text \"USB/AC charger disconnected\" should be displayed below.
Confirm that there\'s a file named \"music.mp3\" stored on the SD card. The file \"music.mp3\" should be played through the device\'s external speakers when you open this test.
Confirm that the required bmp file is on the SD card. Confirm that the colors are consistently displayed across the whole screen. Make sure there are no irregular bright spots and dark spots.

Test instructions:

1.Tap the Camera button below to enter rear Camera interface
2.Make sure the flash is enabled
3.Tap the shutter button
4.Tap the Check icon. The system will save the photo automatically.
5.The photo you took should be displayed below. Tap "Delete" to complete the test.

Test instructions:

1.Tap the Camera button below to enter front Camera interface
2.Tap the shutter button
3.Tap the Check icon. The system will save the photo automatically.
4.The photo you took should be displayed below. Tap "Delete" to complete the test.
Can\'t take photo. SD card is full.
The corresponding GPS info should be displayed below.
This will test the device\'s FM function.
The amount of battery charge should be expressed as a percentage below.
When OTG device is connected, the text \"USB OTG device detected\" should be displayed below.
When OTG device is removed, the text \"USB OTG device removed\" should be displayed below.
